# Alembic Migrations

For convenience and as schema changes over time and iterations, it must be versioned and reproducible at any time, thats why the schema changes are tracked using alembic.
The project it's going to be divided into two main branches `main` where the common PostgresSQL definitions reside and `timescale`, my favorite flavor of Postgres when we are dealing with a bast amount of time date.

With that being said, we can reproduce the database schema using only basic Postgres definition or, we can upgrade up our database with the use of **hypertables**, in any case we can just upgrade from a new fresh database that alembic will handle the heavy work for us.

